data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104utk1665702992506.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/utk1665702992506.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/utk1665702992506.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"utk1665702992506\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Preparing to Install and Run Uniface on Unix and Linux\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When installing Uniface on Unix platforms, you need to create an environment for Uniface. If the Uniface Router and the Uniface Server are to run under different accounts, the Uniface Router needs to run under the root account.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"utk1665702992506__li_d28694e1_d28695e1_d28696e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a user ID for Uniface, for example, user <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface</code>, or use an existing account.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"utk1665702992506__li_d28697e1_d28698e1_d28699e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"utk1665702992506__p_d65867e1_d65868e1_d65869e1\">Create a home directory for this user.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\"> The location suggested by the installer is in the home directory of the user\n               running the installer. You can keep this suggestion or change it to another location\n               to which this user has write access.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"utk1665702992506__li_d28700e1_d28701e1_d28702e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set up the user environment for running Uniface after installation:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"utk1665702992506__li_d28703e1_d28704e1_d28705e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"utk1665702992506__p_d65870e1_d65871e1_d65872e1\">Make sure that any setup scripts for DBMS,\n                     network, or GUI products are executed. Depending on your system, setup scripts\n                     might already exist in the global profile for all users. If not, you can put\n                     them in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.profile</span> file for the Uniface user account. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Consult your DBMS documentation for information on any quotas that need to\n                     be enabled for the Uniface account.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"utk1665702992506__li_d28706e1_d28707e1_d28708e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Install and configure the Sentinel RMS License Manager, if you are using\n                     Network licensing. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fnb1665702748208.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnb1665702748208.html\" title=\"The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager (also known as the RMS Server) enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments.\">Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"utk1665702992506__note_w1762ab1b5b1b5b3b3b3b1_w1763ab1b5b1b5b3b3b3_w1764ab1b5b1b5b3b3_w1765ab1b5b1b5b3_w1766ab1b5b1b5_w1767ab1b5b1_w1768ab1b5_w1769ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This is not required if you are using Sentinel cloud-leased\n                        licenses on Linux. In this case, the license environment is automatically\n                        configured as part of the installation process.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mac1665702749697.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Installing Uniface on Unix and Linux</a><p>The Uniface installation program and related files are provided in a .tar file. After extracting the file you can run the Uniface installer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Preparing to Install and Run Uniface on Unix and Linux Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Preparing to Install and Run Uniface on Unix and Linux When installing Uniface on Unix platforms, you need to create an environment for Uniface. If the Uniface Router and the Uniface Server are to run under different accounts, the Uniface Router needs to run under the root account. Create a user ID for Uniface, for example, user uniface , or use an existing account. Create a home directory for this user. The location suggested by the installer is in the home directory of the user running the installer. You can keep this suggestion or change it to another location to which this user has write access. Set up the user environment for running Uniface after installation: Make sure that any setup scripts for DBMS, network, or GUI products are executed. Depending on your system, setup scripts might already exist in the global profile for all users. If not, you can put them in the .profile file for the Uniface user account. Consult your DBMS documentation for information on any quotas that need to be enabled for the Uniface account. Install and configure the Sentinel RMS License Manager, if you are using Network licensing. For more information, see Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux . Note: This is not required if you are using Sentinel cloud-leased licenses on Linux. In this case, the license environment is automatically configured as part of the installation process. Related Links Installing Uniface on Unix and Linux The Uniface installation program and related files are provided in a .tar file. After extracting the file you can run the Uniface installer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}